OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1780330269
OL,3,CFive new llamas join research herd at
OL,4,CReading farm used to help treat viruses
OL,6,FFive llamas have joined the herd at
OL,7,Fthe University of Reading's Centre for
OL,8,FDairy Research, bringing the total
OL,9,Fnumber on the farm to 23.
OL,11,FDenzil, Marlene, Raquel, Rodney and
OL,12,FTrigger arrived at the CEDAR facility
OL,13,Fat Arborfield in February.
OL,15,FThe five join three llamas born at the
OL,16,Ffarm in the past year - Bella, Donna
OL,17,Fand Gandolph - as well as an older
OL,18,Festablished herd.
OL,20,FOne of the herd is also expected to
OL,21,Fgive birth later this summer.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/7
